    <h1>Puzzle Games</h1>
    <br>
    <p>
        Puzzle games are a genre of video games that challenge players problem-solving skills, logic, and creativity. These games often involve tasks that require players to arrange pieces, solve riddles, or navigate obstacles to reach a goal. Puzzle games have been a key part of the gaming landscape, appealing to players who enjoy mental challenges and a sense of accomplishment from overcoming tricky situations.
    </p>
    <br>
    <p>
        Known for their <strong>strategic thinking</strong>, <strong>critical reasoning</strong>, and <strong>mental stimulation</strong>, puzzle games come in many forms, from classic tile-matching games like Tetris to complex escape-room-style experiences. The genre is widely appreciated for its ability to offer relaxing yet challenging gameplay that rewards patience and perseverance.
    </p>
    <br>
    <p>
        Puzzle games are available on various platforms, offering players a wide range of difficulty levels. Whether it is solving intricate puzzles in games like The Witness or enjoying the simplicity of Sudoku, puzzle games continue to captivate a diverse audience, from casual gamers to those looking for deep, engaging mental exercises.
    </p>

</section>

